/**
 * ============================================================================
 * InSight Survey Comparison Dashboard
 * ============================================================================
 * Champlain College Career Collaborative
 *
 * This React app visualizes Likert-scale survey data from the InSight program.
 * It shows side-by-side histograms of response distributions across cohorts,
 * overlays curve fits (Gaussian or KDE), and provides a mean score comparison.
 *
 * HOW TO UPDATE DATA:
 * -------------------
 * Data is loaded from src/data.json, generated by the build-data.js script.
 *
 *   1. Drop new Canvas CSV exports into the Kickoff/ or Exit/ folders
 *   2. Run: node build-data.js
 *   3. The app hot-reloads automatically
 *
 * Each dataset in data.json has this shape:
 *
 *   {
 *     "name": "Exit - Class of 2027",     // Display label in charts
 *     "type": "Exit",                      // "Kickoff" or "Exit" (drives aggregation)
 *     "cohort": "Class of 2027",           // Section label from Canvas
 *     "n": 250,                            // Total respondents
 *     "questions": {
 *       "Identify personal values": {
 *         "Very untrue of me": 3,
 *         "Somewhat untrue of me": 8,
 *         "Neutral": 20,
 *         "Somewhat true of me": 95,
 *         "Very true of me": 124
 *       },
 *       // ... all 20 questions with their 5 Likert counts
 *     }
 *   }
 *
 * See README.md for full documentation.
 *
 * ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW:
 * ----------------------
 * The app has four main view modes, all sharing the same dataset selection
 * and color management:
 *
 *   1. Histograms ("grid"): A 20-chart grid showing per-question Likert
 *      distributions with optional curve fit overlays (MoM, LSQ, KDE).
 *      Clicking a chart opens an expanded modal with PNG export.
 *
 *   2. Means ("means"): Horizontal bar chart of mean Likert scores (-2 to +2)
 *      for each question, grouped by dataset. The "report-ready" view.
 *
 *   3. Delta ("delta"): Side-by-side comparison of exactly 2 datasets showing
 *      per-question mean shift and Cohen's d effect size. The "leadership
 *      slide" view for demonstrating program impact.
 *
 *   4. Categories ("categories"): Groups the 20 questions into the three
 *      InSight pillars (Wellbeing, Financial Literacy, Career Positioning)
 *      and shows aggregate + per-question means per category.
 *
 * DEPENDENCIES:
 * - react (included with create-react-app)
 * - recharts (npm install recharts)
 * - html2canvas (npm install html2canvas) - for PNG export in the modal
 * ============================================================================
 */

